Among the physicians of his time, Ibn Abī l-Bayān was the most capable in compounding drugs and knowing the appropriate quantities and weights. So much so that when patients with various illnesses, even rare ones, came to consult him, he would dictate on the spot, in accordance with just what that patient required, medical prescriptions for compound drugs such as pastilles (
al-aqrāṣ
), medicinal powders (
al-safūfāt
), syrups (
al-ashribah
) and so forth. These prescriptions were of the utmost quality and very well designed.

